cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the problem of identifying heavy-hitters in network traffic streams, which is a key issue in network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the threat model of DDoS attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed algorithms and data structures involve hashing and efficient storage, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of hardware implementation, which is related to cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of summaries of network streams, which is a topic in cs.IT (Information Theory).
